# Changelog

All notable changes to PDF Text-to-Speech Reader will be documented here.

Format based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/).

## [1.0.0] — 2026-02-12

### Added
- PDF upload with drag & drop support
- Text-to-speech with 50+ browser voices
- Real-time word-by-word highlighting
- Sentence highlighting mode
- Adjustable reading speed (0.5× to 3×)
- Voice picker with search and preview
- Right-click word dictionary lookup
- Light, Dark, and Sepia themes
- Keyboard shortcuts (Space, Esc, ?)
- Zoom controls (Ctrl+scroll, buttons, fit-to-width)
- Page navigation and jump-to-page
- Human-sounding pause system (punctuation-aware)
- Heading detection with emphasis
- Virtualized page rendering (handles 300+ page PDFs)
- Auto-scroll to current word
- "Go to Current Word" button
- Welcome modal with instructions
- Toast notifications
- Responsive footer
- 100% local processing — no data uploaded anywhere
- Progressive loading for large documents
- Focus Reading Mode
